<paragraph id="5E555E77FFD4334DFF52FD497105FCDE" blockId="12.[166,1225,651,998]" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">
R e m a r k. All the three nominal species were described based of the specimens from the same series collected in 
<collectingCountry id="26FD1EE7FFD4334DFE7EFD697046FD5E" box="[503,629,683,710]" name="Cameroon" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
and showing no essential differences in the body size, coloration and vestiture. I consider these specimens to be conspecific and synonymize the species names based on them as name-bearing 
<typeStatus id="8151E0D5FFD4334DFD7BFD297101FC9E" box="[754,818,747,774]" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">types</typeStatus>
. Th e number of scutellar setae vary from four through five to six in this species and also in 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFD4334DFCA3FCCE7193FCBD" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1914" box="[810,928,779,806]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oculata">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFCA3FCCE710EFCBE" box="[810,829,780,806]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFCC3FCC97193FCBD" box="[842,928,779,805]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">oculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFD4334DFC24FCCE760CFCBD" authorityName="Seguy" authorityYear="1933" box="[941,1087,779,806]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latipennis">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFC24FCCE71F3FCBE" box="[941,960,780,806]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFC44FCC9760CFCBD" box="[973,1087,779,805]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">latipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and related species and cannot serve ever for distinguishing species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5E555E77FFD4334DFF52FC897669FC7E" blockId="12.[166,1225,651,998]" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">
The nominal genera 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFD4334DFE50FC8E7127FCFE" authority="Enderlein, 1942" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1942" box="[473,788,843,870]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Dicrostira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFE50FC8E707DFCFD" box="[473,590,844,869]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">Dicrostira</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="3A7B2386FFD4334DFDD1FC897127FCFE" author="Enderlein, G." box="[600,788,843,870]" pageId="12" pageNumber="207" pagination="98 - 134" refId="ref11407" refString="Enderlein, G. 1942. Klassifikation der Pyrgotiden. Sitzungsberichte der Gesellschaft Naturforschenden Freunde zu Berlin, (1941) (2), 98 - 134." type="journal article" year="1942">Enderlein, 1942</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFC96FC8E717BFCFE" bold="true" box="[799,840,844,870]" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">syn</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFCD3FC8E7158FCFE" bold="true" box="[858,875,844,870]" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">n</emphasis>
. and 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFC3AFC8E7677FCFD" box="[947,1092,844,869]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">Hexamerinx</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="3A7B2386FFD4334DFBC6FC8972EDFC1E" author="Enderlein, G." pageId="12" pageNumber="207" pagination="98 - 134" refId="ref11407" refString="Enderlein, G. 1942. Klassifikation der Pyrgotiden. Sitzungsberichte der Gesellschaft Naturforschenden Freunde zu Berlin, (1941) (2), 98 - 134." type="journal article" year="1942">Enderlein, 1942</bibRefCitation>
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFF61FCAE7322FC1E" bold="true" box="[232,273,876,902]" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">syn</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFEABFCAE7300FC1E" bold="true" box="[290,307,876,902]" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">n</emphasis>
. were based on the height of gena and number of scutellar setae, which are common for the whole group of species, related to 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFD4334DFC8CFC4E71B5FC3D" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1914" box="[773,902,907,934]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latigenis">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFC8CFC4E712BFC3E" box="[773,792,908,934]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFCAFFC4971B5FC3D" box="[806,902,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">latigenis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFD4334DFC4AFC4E7668FC3D" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1843" box="[963,1115,907,934]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferruginea">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFC4AFC4E71E5FC3E" box="[963,982,908,934]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFC6DFC497668FC3D" box="[996,1115,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">ferruginea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus id="8151E0D5FFD4334DFB1FFC4976FBFC3E" box="[1174,1224,907,934]" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFD4334DFEAEFC69738CFC5D" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1843" box="[295,447,939,965]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFEAEFC69738CFC5D" box="[295,447,939,965]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">Campylocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and have no value even for recognition of species. I therefore consider them congeneric and synonymize the generic names with 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFD4334DFC32FC097660FC7D" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1843" box="[955,1107,971,997]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFC32FC097660FC7D" box="[955,1107,971,997]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">Campylocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
